Middle School QA Panel

Penn Yan Middle School
August 21 at 7:10 AM ·

Last Chance to get your questions in!

https://forms.gle/4GFDD5XPMg74pETz6

For incoming 6th Graders, their parents and families, or other MS Students and Families - What do you want to know before beginning your Middle School Journey? If you've already navigated through 6th Grade, what do you wish you'd been prepared for?

It's a nerve wracking time entering a new building, and this year we had a lot of unknowns coming into the Fall. Ask our team! We're delighted to answer your questions, respond to concerns, and just generally start a dialogue with our new students to make the transition from PYE to the Middle School as seamless as possible. We have so much to offer and want to share all the possibilities with you!

Fill out the form, ask a question or 3, and we'll respond in our next video, the final of our 5 part Miniseries 'Middle School Rocks' - If you haven't seen them yet, make sure to check out 1-4 here on Facebook!

text: Letter to families for additional updates on School reopening and where we're currently at as of 7/17/2020. More information will be coming as more information has been directed to the School. We'll continue to keep you updated.

post_text:
Our district has created a brief survey to better understand the perspectives our stakeholders have regarding the reopening of our schools for students in September 2020. The purpose of this survey is to collect feedback to help us in our decision making. Please do not interpret your answers as choices for the Fall.

The COVID-19 pandemic required significant action and disruption from our traditional face-to-face instructional model. The information and data that is gathered from this survey will help our district best prepare and develop plans, protocols, and safety measures that are appropriate and align with our stakeholders' expectations. Our top priority is the health, safety, and welfare of our students, staff, and families.

Thank you for sharing feedback on these topics that relate to the reopening of schools in the Fall.

Responses will be accepted until Friday, July 17th.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/pyreopeningfeedback

post_text: The Penn Yan Athletic Department will be celebrating all of our athletes who received awards during our 54th Annual Sports Awards last week. We will celebrate the athletes on Tuesday, June 9th from 5:00pm - 8:00pm during a Drive-Thru Awards Distribution. Athletes are invited to drive-thru and pick up their awards and stop for a quick photo op with their coach. Athletes can bring as many people as they want to celebrate with them but only the athlete will be allowed to exit their vehicle. A drive by photo opportunity will be available for family to take pictures from their vehicles. The coach and athlete will need to wear masks and practice safe social distancing. The drive thru will take place in the parking lot off of Liberty Street next to the tennis courts. Athletes will receive their assigned times in an email sent directly to their school email. http://edl.io/n1241721

Voting for PYCSD Budget Vote and Board of Education Members

In accordance with Executive Order from the Governor, the Budget Vote and School Board Election will be held remotely, by ABSENTEE BALLOT ONLY.

Absentee Ballots are being mailed to ALL QUALIFIED VOTERS of this school district and should be received by Thursday, June 4.

Completed absentee ballots must be received by the District Clerk by 5:00 p.m. on June 9, 2020.

Please be sure to allow adequate time for ballots to be returned by mail, using the pre-addressed postage-paid envelope that will be provided by the District. Or, ballots may also be returned in person by placing them in the District Office Drop Box. The District Office is located in the Elementary School at One School Drive.

The District Office will also be open for in person drop off between 7:30 a.m. and 3:00 p.m. on June 4, 5, and 8 or between 7:30 a.m. and 5:00 p.m. on June 9.

If you have questions regarding absentee ballots, please contact Kathleen Champlin, District Clerk, at 315-536-3371. http://edl.io/n1239336

Today’s Senior Bow is for the one and only Cami Webber!

Cami has shown tremendous growth as an actor over the last four years, which can be chalked up to her hard work and dedication to her craft. We will miss you next year, Cami!

Dear students and families,

As we will all be home for an extended period of time, the school nurses would like to gently remind you that the best place for accurate information regarding COVID-19 is the CDC, Center for Disease Control www.cdc.gov and the NYSDOH, New York State Department of Health www.health.ny.gov websites. Not Facebook, Instagram or Twitter.

Call your doctor: If you think you have been exposed to COVID-19 and develop a fever and symptoms, such as cough or difficulty breathing, call your healthcare provider for medical advice. (Directions from the CDC website)

Thank you all for your commitment to keeping yourselves and those that you love healthy. It really does take a community coming together and doing the right thing by each other to stop the spread of this virus. Take care of yourselves, remember to smile and count all of the goodness in each day and we’ll get through this together!

PYCSD School Nurses

Please note that you will need to present identification at the time of pick up. Monday and Tuesday are the ideal days for pick-up, as the building will be staffed; after March 17, the nurses will not be on campus. shared_text:
Penn Yan Academy Drama Club
February 15 at 7:24 PM ·

Today, we need to give a shout-out to all the work that goes on behind the scenes to make our productions a success. Not everyone realizes just how much time and energy goes into the “back end” of our shows. We have already had two set-building days and have spent hours gathering props, furniture, and costumes. Today, we spent 6 hours at our first tech work day, where we had crews working on costumes, light design plots, painting the set, setting up all the sound equipment, and numerous other tasks. That still leaves our “dry” and “wet” tech days (often all-day affairs) and tons of work that happens in patches outside of assigned work time. Fortunately, we have tons of students and adults who are so hard-working and so willing to give their time and effort to make our shows wonderful! Great job, everyone - and THANK YOU!

post_text: Congratulations to Kayla Anderson, 1 of 2 winners for the 2019 Yates County Distinguished Youth Award. This award is presented to a Yates County resident between 11-21 that has shown outstanding or extraordinary contribution to community or family. Kayla was nominated by Patti Harling and Erin Johnson for being a leader among her peers while being dedicated to academic excellence and having a positive community impact via various projects and volunteer efforts. Kayla, a Senior at PYA, is a member of NHS, Rotary Interact, Class Treasurer, Yearbook Editor, VP of Art Club, Band Council Treasurer, International Club President, and a Youth Rep for Milo Center Methodist Church. The letter of recommendation made it apparent that Kayla brings a positive impact and our community is better for having her in it.

shared_text:
Penn Yan Academy Drama Club
February 12 at 6:47 AM ·

Tonight was the first stumble-through of act I for Bright Star! To those unfamiliar with the term, the stumble-through is the first time actors run through an act in its entirety, putting together all the pieces they have been working on (blocking, choreo, acting, vocals, etc.). It is often very difficult and VERY rough as it is a lot of moving parts coming together at once, but it is useful for identifying needs moving forward. Add to that the fact that it is the first time actors cannot use their scripts at all (“off-book”), and it can sometimes be a recipe for disaster. Tonight’s stumble-through, though, could not have gone smoother - it was abundantly clear how much time and work everyone has been putting in and how professional they all are. We are so proud of them!

Remember - be there March 12-15 to see this wonderful production!

The Penn Yan Lady Mustangs girls basketball program would like to thank you from the bottom of our hearts for helping us support Pam Whitford and her battle with cancer this past Saturday during our 4th Annual Hoops for Hope event! With your help, we were able to raise $2,286.85!!

Donations: $624.35
T-shirts Sales: $787.50
50/50 (donated back!): $229.00
Cookie Sale: $140.00
Gift Raffle: $506.00

A HUGE thank you to our amazing community for donating gift certificates and various gifts to the raffle! Thank you to Coach Deb Curbeau and the Penn Yan Lady Mustangs mod squad for helping to run the event! Thank you to all who put in effort to sell t-shirts! And a huge thank you to all who attended and supported the event!! Together, WE made a difference!!! ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜 THANK YOU! 🙏🏻
